module.description: The MIB module for IEEE 1609.3v3 full use entities. iso(1) iso-identified-organization(3) ieee(111) standards-association-numbered-series-standards(2) wave-stds(1609) dot3(3) v3mib(3)

table.name: dot3StationConfigTable
table.description: Station Configuration attributes pertinent to Networking Services. In tabular form to allow for multiple instances on an agent.

row.name: dot3StationConfigEntry
row.description: An entry in the dot3StationConfigTable. Each entry corresponds to one of multiple IEEE 802.11 interfaces (if present).

column.name: dot3StationConfigIndex
column.description: Index to the Station Config Table.

column.name: dot3CchAccessImplemented
column.description: Indicates whether the device supports operation on the control channel.

column.name: dot3SchAccessImplemented
column.description: Indicates whether the device supports operation on any service channel.

column.name: dot3IpV6Implemented
column.description: Indicates whether the device supports IPv6 data exchange.

column.name: dot3UdpImplemented
column.description: Indicates whether the device supports the User Datagram Protocol.

column.name: dot3TcpImplemented
column.description: Indicates whether the device supports the Transmission Control Protocol.

column.name: dot3WsmpImplemented
column.description: Indicates whether the device supports the WAVE Short Message Protocol.

column.name: dot3UserRoleImplemented
column.description: Indicates whether the device implements the User role.

column.name: dot3ProviderRoleImplemented
column.description: Indicates whether the device implements the Provider role.

column.name: dot3TimingAdvertisementServiceImplemented
column.description: Indicates whether the device supports the generation of Timing Advertisement frames at the request of higher layers.

scalar.name: dot3NumberOfChannelsSupported
scalar.description: The number of radio channels that may be simultaneously accessed by the device.

scalar.name: dot3AdvertiserIdentifier
scalar.description: A text string optionally sent in the WSA identifying the service provider device.

scalar.name: dot3RegistrationPort
scalar.description: UDP port number used for registration of external applications.

scalar.name: dot3WsmMaxLength
scalar.description: Maximum size in octets of the variable length portion of a WSM, including data. The default value is 1400. Max value is 802.11 MAC MSDU size minus EtherType size (2304 minus 2 = 2302).

column.name: dot3ChannelServiceRequestTableIndex
column.description: Table index.

column.name: dot3ChannelServiceRequestChannelIdentifier
column.description: Requested channel identifier, as defined in IEEE 802.11.

column.name: dot3ChannelServiceRequestTimeSlot
column.description: Time slot(s) to which the request applies.

column.name: dot3ChannelServiceRequestStatus
column.description: Current status of the request.

column.name: dot3WsmServiceRequestTableIndex
column.description: Table index.

column.name: dot3WsmServiceRequestPsid
column.description: Provider Service Identifier to be internally routed on receipt.

column.name: dot3ProviderServiceRequestTableIndex
column.description: Table index.

column.name: dot3WsaType
column.description: Security processing to be applied to the transmitted WSA.

column.name: dot3ProviderServiceIdentifier
column.description: PSID associated with the request.

column.name: dot3ProviderServiceContext
column.description: PSC info provided by the requester.

column.name: dot3ProviderChannelAccess
column.description: Access type associated with the request.

column.name: dot3ProviderBestAvailable
column.description: When true, indicates the best available service channel should be used; when false indicates the dot3ProviderServiceChannelNumber should be used.

column.name: dot3ProviderOperatingClass
column.description: Operating class of the associated service channel, as defined in IEEE Std 802.11.

column.name: dot3ProviderServiceChannelNumber
column.description: Indicate a requested service channel number, as defined in IEEE 802.11.

column.name: dot3ProviderWsaChannelNumber
column.description: Indicate a requested service or control channel number on which to transmit WSAs, as defined in IEEE 802.11.

column.name: dot3ProviderRepeatRate
column.description: Number of WSAs to be transmitted each 5 seconds.

column.name: dot3ProviderIpService
column.description: Indicates whether or not the requested service supports IP traffic.

column.name: dot3ProviderIpv6Address
column.description: IP address of the server associated with the requested service.

column.name: dot3ProviderMacAddress
column.description: MAC address of the server associated with the requested service if different from the transmitting device.

column.name: dot3ProviderServicePort
column.description: Transport layer port number associated with the requested service.

column.name: dot3ProviderRcpiThreshold
column.description: The recommended power of received WSAs for accepting the advertised service.

column.name: dot3ProviderWsaCountThreshold
column.description: The recommended number of received WSAs before accepting the advertised service.

column.name: dot3ProviderWsaCountThresholdInterval
column.description: The number of 100ms intervals over which to count received WSAs before accepting the advertised service.

column.name: dot3ProviderServiceStatus
column.description: Current status of the requested provider service request.

column.name: dot3ProviderChannelInfoTableIndex
column.description: Table index.

column.name: dot3ProviderChannelInfoOperatingClass
column.description: Operating Class.

column.name: dot3ProviderChannelInfoChannelNumber
column.description: Channel Number.

column.name: dot3ProviderChannelInfoAdaptable
column.description: Indicates whether data rate is fixed or maximum value.

column.name: dot3ProviderChannelInfoDataRate
column.description: Channel data rate in increments of 500kbit/s, from 1 Mb/s to 63.5 Mb/s.

column.name: dot3ProviderChannelInfoTransmitPowerLevel
column.description: Channel EIRP transmit power.

column.name: dot3ProviderChannelInfoEdcaBkCWmin
column.description: This attribute shall specify the value of the minimum size of the window that shall be used by a STA for a particular AC for generating a random number for the backoff. The value of this attribute shall be such that it could always be expressed in the form of 2X - 1, where X is an integer.

column.name: dot3ProviderChannelInfoEdcaBkCWmax
column.description: This attribute shall specify the value of the maximum size of the window that shall be used by a STA for a particular AC for generating a random number for the backoff. The value of this attribute shall be such that it could always be expressed in the form of 2X - 1, where X is an integer.

column.name: dot3ProviderChannelInfoEdcaBkAifsn
column.description: This attribute shall specify the number of slots, after a SIFS duration, that the STA shall sense the medium idle either before transmitting or executing a backoff.

column.name: dot3ProviderChannelInfoEdcaBkTxopLimit
column.description: This attribute shall specify the maximum number of microseconds of an EDCA TXOP.

column.name: dot3ProviderChannelInfoEdcaBkMandatory
column.description: This attribute, when TRUE, indicates that admission control is mandatory for the given AC. When False, this attribute indicates that the admission control is not mandatory for the given AC.

column.name: dot3UserServiceRequestTableIndex
column.description: Table index.

column.name: dot3UserServiceRequestType
column.description: Request type.

column.name: dot3UserServiceRequestProviderServiceIdentifier
column.description: Requested PSID for matching.

column.name: dot3UserServiceRequestProviderServiceContext
column.description: Requested PSC for matching.

column.name: dot3UserServiceRequestPriority
column.description: Request priority.

column.name: dot3UserServiceRequestWsaTypes
column.description: Requested WSA type(s) for matching.

column.name: dot3UserServiceRequestSourceMacAddress
column.description: Requested provider for matching.

column.name: dot3UserServiceRequestAdvertiserIdentifier
column.description: Requested Advertiser Identifier for matching.

column.name: dot3UserServiceRequestOperatingClass
column.description: Requested Operating Class for matching.

column.name: dot3UserServiceRequestChannelNumber
column.description: Requested Channel Number for matching.

column.name: dot3UserServiceRequestLinkQuality
column.description: Requested Link Quality for matching.

column.name: dot3UserServiceRequestImmediateAccess
column.description: Indicates the duration of the immediate channel access (during both time slot 0 and time slot 1) in sync intervals. 255 indicates indefinite access. 0 indicates immediate access not requested.

column.name: dot3UserServiceStatus
column.description: Indicates the current status of the request.

column.name: dot3UserAvailableServiceTableIndex
column.description: Table index.

column.name: dot3UserAvailableWsaType
column.description: Security level of the received WSA.

column.name: dot3UserAvailableSecurityResultCode
column.description: Security level of the received WSA.

column.name: dot3UserAvailableGenerationTime
column.description: Generation time of the WSA security information per IEEE Std 1609.2.

column.name: dot3UserAvailableLifetime
column.description: Lifetime of the WSA security information per IEEE Std 1609.2.

column.name: dot3UserAvailableEarliestNextCrlTime
column.description: Expected certificate revocation list time of the WSA security information per IEEE Std 1609.2.

column.name: dot3UserAvailableSourceMacAddress
column.description: Transmitter of the WSA.

column.name: dot3UserAvailableProviderServiceIdentifier
column.description: PSID of the available service.

column.name: dot3UserAvailableProviderServiceContext
column.description: PSC of the available service.

column.name: dot3UserAvailableIpv6Address
column.description: IP address of the service provider.

column.name: dot3UserAvailableServicePort
column.description: Transport protocol port number of the available service.

column.name: dot3UserAvailableProviderMacAddress
column.description: MAC address of the service provider, if different from the provider.

column.name: dot3UserAvailableRcpiThreshold
column.description: Suggested reception level of the received WSA.

column.name: dot3UserAvailableRcpi
column.description: Actual level of the received WSA. Coded per IEEE Std 802.11-2012/18.3.10.7.

column.name: dot3UserAvailableWsaCountThreshold
column.description: Suggested number of received WSA for service acceptance.

column.name: dot3UserAvailableOperatingClass
column.description: Operating Class of the channel.

column.name: dot3UserAvailableChannelNumber
column.description: Number of the SCH associated with the service.

column.name: dot3UserAvailableAdaptable
column.description: Indicates whether data rate is interpreted as maximum allowed value.

column.name: dot3UserAvailableDataRate
column.description: Data rate on the indicated channel, in increments of 500kbit/s from 1 Mb/s to 63.5 Mb/s.

column.name: dot3UserAvailableTransmitPowerLevel
column.description: Power level on the indicated channel.

column.name: dot3UserAvailableChannelAccess
column.description: Indicates the duty cycle of the advertised service.

column.name: dot3UserAvailableAdvertiserIdentifier
column.description: Advertiser Identifier of the advertising device.

column.name: dot3UserAvailableTxLatitude
column.description: Latitude of the advertising device LSB = 1/10 micro degree Providing a range of plus-minus 90 degrees, with 900000001 indicating unavailable.

column.name: dot3UserAvailableTxLongitude
column.description: Longitude of the advertising device LSB = 1/10 micro degree Providing a range of plus-minus 180 degrees, with 1800000001 indicating unavailable.

column.name: dot3UserAvailableTxElevation
column.description: Elevation of the advertising device. 1 decimeter LSB (10 cm) Encode elevations from 0 to 6143.9 meters above the reference ellipsoid as 0x0000 to 0xEFFF. Encode elevations from -409.5 to -0.1 meters, i.e. below the reference ellipsoid, as 0xF001 to 0xFFFF unknown as 0xF000.

column.name: dot3UserAvailableLinkQuality
column.description: Estimated link quality associated with the advertised service.

column.name: dot3UserAvailableServiceStatus
column.description: Indicates whether device resources have been allocated in support of the service.

group.name: dot3UserGroup
group.description: User service request and available service objects

group.name: dot3SecuredUserGroup
group.description: User available service objects related to secured WSAs

compliance.name: dot3Compliance
compliance.description: Describes the requirements for conformance to the IEEE 1609.3 MIB.

option.name: dot3IpV6Group
option.description: This group is mandatory for WAVE devices capable of IPv6 operation.

option.name: dot3WsmpGroup
option.description: This group is mandatory for WAVE devices capable of WSMP operation.

option.name: dot3RegistrationPortGroup
option.description: This group is mandatory for implementations supporting remote service request over an IP network.

option.name: dot3WavRoutingAdvertisement
option.description: This group is mandatory for Providers sending WRAs.

option.name: dot3ChannelInfo
option.description: This group is mandatory for Providers sending WSA Channel Info.

option.name: dot3ProviderGroup
option.description: This group is optional for implementations supporting Provider operation.

option.name: dot3ProviderIpGroup
option.description: This group is optional for Providers of IPv6 services.

option.name: dot3SecuredUserGroup
option.description: This group is optional for User operation with secured WSAs.

option.name: dot3UserGroup
option.description: This group is optional for implementations supporting User operation.

option.name: dot3ChannelRequestGroup
option.description: This group is optional for implementations supporting channel service requests.
